http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/kerala/175-litre-of-liquor-seized/article14596330.ece

In the continuing crackdown on smuggling of liquor from Karnataka into the district ahead of Onam season, Sales Tax Intelligence officials seized 175 litres of Indian-made foreign liquor from an auto rickshaw at Hossangadi.The brew, filled both in bottles and packets, was seized around 9.30 p.m. on Saturday. The occupants of the three-wheeler, found to be bearing fake registration number, fleed from the spot under the cover of darkness, Excise sources here said. The seized liquor along with the vehicle was handed over to the custody of Kumbla Excise Range office, they said. — Staff Reporter